1 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280.4 of Title 59, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The State Commissioner of Health shall promulgate rules to:
5 1. Adopt a set of standards for the approval of certified
6 community health workers' initial coursework or curriculum;
7 2. Establish examination administration requirements for the
8 Department;
9 3. Define minimum qualifications for applicants to be
10 certified; and
11 4. Establish the criteria for granting, renewing, denying,
12 suspending, and revoking a certificate to uphold health standards
13 and safety.
14 B. The Commissioner may also promulgate rules to establish
15 partnerships with faith-based organizations to enhance community
16 health outreach and service delivery, including, but not limited to:
17 1. Recognizing faith-based organizations as eligible entities
18 for community health worker training and certification programs when
19 they meet established state standards;
20 2. Facilitating collaboration between community health workers
21 and faith-based organizations to improve health access, prevention,
22 and health literacy efforts in underserved communities;
23
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1831 Page 4

1 3. Supporting faith-based health initiatives through technical
2 assistance and programmatic support for community health workers
3 working within congregations and religious institutions; and
4 4. Encouraging the integration of community health workers into
5 existing faith-based outreach programs to enhance culturally
6 competent care and strengthen trust in community health efforts.
7 C. The Commissioner shall prescribe fees for the certified
8 community health worker examination, initial certification, and
9 certification renewal.
10 SECTION 6. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
